    # game/areas/peltnorth0structure.rpy:849
    old "She touches the animal, which pays no attention to her presence. “Now I’m {i}really{/i} scared,” she contradicts her words with a gentle smile and shining eyes. “Maybe I should wear something lighter?” \n\nYou nod and engage in a bit of a chit-chat with the entire group, discussing what it takes to take care of a horse. Finally, {color=#f6d6bd}the red-haired woman{/color} leads you under the roof where your palfrey can rest, tethered with a cord to a wooden post, near some old hay. “Once you’re ready, go inside, speak with our boss. Maybe you’re hungry?” \n\nThe other guards return to various chores. They peek at your mount every now and then as they’re splitting firewood, cleaning their clothes, weeding the garden patches, and moving chairs. Two of them are making a rope. You head toward the inn, hearing the piercing scream of a boar from the other side of the yard. "
